lenges? This book seeks to understand the growth and popularity of independent Pentecostal megachurches in Southeast Asia. Using an ethnographic approach, the chapters examine Pentecostal megachurches in Malaysia, Indonesia, the Philippines, and Singapore. Each chapter dwells on the development of the megachurch set against the specific background of the country’s politics and history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aBig churcheszSoutheast Asia. 0aBig churches. 0aChristianityzSoutheast Asia. 0aChristianity. 0aChurch growthzSoutheast Asia. 0aChurch growth. 0aPentecostal churcheszSoutheast Asia. 0aPentecostal churches. 0aPentecostalismzSoutheast Asia. 0aPentecostalism. 0aSoutheast Asia. 4aSociology of Religion. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology of Religion.2bisacsh1 aChao, En-Chieh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChong, Terence, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChong, Terence, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aChoong, Chong Eu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoh, Daniel P. S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoon, Chang-Yau, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSerrano Cornelio, Jayeel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTejedo, Joel A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYip, Jeaney, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2018z978311071955008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060677540uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/978981478689840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789814786898423Cove